  "text": "A functional dependency X → A is a full functional dependency if removal of any attribute B from X means that the dependency does not hold any more; that is, for any attribute B∈X, (X -B) does not functionally determine A. A functional dependency X→A is a partial dependency if A is not a key-attribute and some attribute B∈X can be removed from X and the dependency still holds; that is, for some B∈X, (X -B) → A [CITATION_1] . Full and partial dependencies are generated as follows:",
